{
    "description_long": "This is a stone grave monument featuring a central vertical pillar topped with a sculpted eagle, flanked by two curved upright slabs. The base is constructed from rough-cut stone blocks, with a raised platform and steps leading up to the main section. Floral arrangements, both real and artificial, are placed on the platform, suggesting recent visitation. The monument includes several inscribed plaques, some of which are set into the stonework, while others are mounted on the upright slabs. The overall structure is robust and solemn, with a mix of smooth and rough stone textures. The eagle sculpture and the arrangement of the slabs give the monument a distinctive and dignified appearance.",
